text: Sabine County is a county in the U.S. state of Texas. In the 2020 census, 9,894 people lived there. The county seat is Hemphill. The county was founded on December 14, 1837, and named for the Sabine River. It is on the eastern border with Louisiana. ==References== Category:1830s establishments in the Republic of Texas Category:1837 establishments in the United States Category:Texas counties
